The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Wednesday, November 06, 2002 				 SA recall McKenzie, Elworthy
				 	 McKENZIE: Back after eight months 																								Johannesburg: Batsman Neil McKenzie, veteran seamer Steve Elworthy and allrounder Andrew Hall have been recalled to the South Africa squad for the first of two Tests against Sri Lanka starting here Friday.																								McKenzie, out of favour since South Africas 1-2 home series defeat by Australia in March, returns after a big century against the Sri Lankans for South Africa A at the expense of Martin van Jaarsveld.																								Hall, named one of South Africas five players of the year last month, returns after featuring in the home series against the Australians.																								THE SQUAD																								Shaun Pollock (captain), Herschelle Gibbs, Graeme Smith, Gary Kirsten, Jacques Kallis, Neil McKenzie, Ashwell Prince, Mark Boucher, Andrew Hall, Claude Henderson, Makhaya Ntini, Steve Elworthy, Mornantau Hayward. (REUTERS)
